t: Leukopenia - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics
s: Leukopenia typically refers to a decrease in circulating white blood cells (WBCs) below 4.4 × 109 cells/L. As neutrophils and lymphocytes are the most abundant WBCs in peripheral blood, leukopenia may occur in the setting of lymphopenia, neutropenia, or both.
